            <Title>Zadane</Title>
            <Text>Zadane
17 • Low Weir/Freedom

Role in Story
With a strong southern perspective, she reveals life and thought in the south lands while bringing a fresh perspective into the Fatunik Lands.   Allane's mother?

Goal
To learn. To grow. To promote the influence of Malavorra and the River-Soul worldview.

Physical Description
Wild hair. Big everything. Female presentation.

Personality
Big

Occupation
Visitors guide. Occasional farm hand

Habits/Mannerisms
Enjoys telling the stories and singing the songs of Malavorra, Low Weir and the River-Soul. 

Background
Raised by an Dauni Vakasaqua family in the southern Weir Lands.

Internal Conflicts
As much as she likes Low Weir and her job, Zadane is intensely curious about the other provinces. She resents somewhat being kept down on the farm. Likes to wander about the Weir Lands, has also made occasional trips to Eelan and the Settanarune. Has never been to the Fatunik provinces.

External Conflicts
Near the end of the tale, she gives us an angle into another story...

She stumbles upon a cave entrance that leads to an underground facility beneath Low Weir. Astonished to learn that the elders keep secrets from the collective. And that the nature of those secrets -- genetic engineering, weapons, flight-related technology -- may contradict widely-propagated Dauni Vakasaqua and Settan pacifistic views. 

