            <Title>Cool Waters</Title>
            <Text>Cool Waters
Card Number: 12
+ / -  Main conflicts in this scene.

Bu'ruq, Mu'ray and Monmar Massachawa sneak into Juuj, where they encounter sint communities  in the underground caverns and waterways way beneath the Deep Pool, as well as huge marine worms who may or may not be sentient.

They set off a tremor that sends ripples upwards to the Deep Pool of Juuj.

&gt; &lt;  Main events, resolutions, actions in this scene.

MM's team locate Quinn and let him know they are there. She offers him an escape plan but he chooses not to escape with them because he wants to present his Argument to the Elders.  She impresses SPQ with her rebel spirit, and she with his, sparking a kind of empathetic emotional electrical storm.  Think of the whale-phoenix dyad gathering its strength in the first story of Zhuangzi, preparing to explore the vast otherness of the universe.  

The Elders are the doves, the pigeons, the guppies, the trout darting about, satisfied with their knowledge of things, dismissive of the vastness they cannot comprehend.

The Elders read the disturbance as an omen. But of what? They are not sure.

Timeline

Action --&gt; Following directly from chapter 6. While the respectable folks in the Outer Lands are preparing for war and legal battles, MM and her gang are taking direct action.
Beauty

The Deep Pool lies at the center of large cenote, where the Elders gather at its periphery as the Sun reflects on its surface. Their song is one of whispers.

Many creatures live underground and raise their kids there, often having built cozy alcove-like bed clusters around a play space with curtains (not doors) separating it from a common space. We'll see this pattern reproduced in the Fatunik-style Brood Houses, providing a visual tie between the species' experiences after the Catastrophe.
Humor

MM treats the "great and terrible Oz" Elders like a child's toy. No respect. 
Truth

The pelvis is the second-largest body mass after the ribcage. 
Impact

Cool, we've learned multiple emergency climbing techniques: chimneying, manteling, stemming, a heel hook, crimper holds and pincher holds.

