            <Title>Iyaghold</Title>
            <Synopsis>Location Name</Synopsis>
            <Text>Iyaghold


Type of Location

The only fortified military encampment in the Kahila Lands, the fortress of Iyaghold guards the northern border of Kahilabequa from the central Fatunik province to Tabloonque.

Role in Story

Near the conclusion of the Kahila Wars, the Fatunika occupied a strip of land connecting the two Kahila provinces, between Juukal and the Rune of Bye, incorporating the Kahila Strip in Juukal.

This remains a sore point of contention between the Kahilafolk and the Authority.

The strip is guarded by a sizable Fatunik encampment at the western end of the strip, actually located just over the border in Tabloonque. The establishment of this permanent camp, seen as a symbol of occupation, was particularly galling to the Kahilabequan elements who had sought a just and peaceable accomodation to end the hostilities. Their response when the Helipticon refused to remove their camp was the establishment of the Iyaghold. 
