            <Title>Mikel Moballeq</Title>
            <Text>Mikel Moballeq
70s or 80s • Location

Role in Story
Descendent of the original settlers of Mobalbesq, elder of the Mobal Beshqi, Mikel Moballeq is happy to provide a perspective on Fatunik authority from an indigenous mostly-beklek tribe who have developed their own autonomous understanding of Catastrophic ideology.  

He offers a path to a cosmopolitan world view within the mix of eastern Saskan thinking and tradition. 

The King. The Prince. A Wise Father.

Need some equivalent characters for other key regions, etc.… 

		Who is actually part of the Authority?
		Who leads the Riders Council?
		Who is the head of the Empafarasi? 
		Who are the Elders of the Eelani?
		Who are the heads of the bitamin and romperi clans?
		Who are the heads of the main Guilds?
		…
Goal
We might think of Mikel M as someone who presents a Shi’a-like take as an alternative to the Sunni-like orthodoxy of the Authority. Or a Mahayana riff far afield from the core Fatunik Theravada old school vehicle, while still remaining true to the main themes of the tradition. 

Physical Description
Wounded, troubled, but still standing. Mikel, like the Mobal Beshqi clan in general, endures.

Personality
Loquaicious, well-versed in Fatunik theology and terminology.  Has ability and willingness to be syncretic and to be open to cosmopolitan views that endears him to many southerners.  

Occupation
Effectively the governor of the province of Mobalbesq, though such titles do not officially exist.  Jefe of a large estate in the Mobalbesq, involved in numerous enterprises. Has close connections to the Fatunik authorities. Also on good terms with Riders, various southern guilds and tribes, sea-borne connections of various types, the Byenung complex of organizations and families, connections with influential parties in the Nye Lands, and, via Ríkila, even to certain Kahila tribes and organizations. 

He is definitely the person you want to know if you want to get things done in Mobalbesq.

Habits/Mannerisms
Bisexual. Vegetarian. Has had many partners and admirers. As a person high up in the hierarchy, is free by Fatunik norms to openly express a male gender, which he does, but in an over-bearing way only on rare occasions when he needs to throw his considerable weight around, particularly with Fatunik characters. 

Background
Many stories and songs about his origins.  Maybe Mikel was born in faraway Shanowa and came to the Saskan Lands as a teen-ager.  He refuses to discuss his early childhood. Maybe he was captured and mistreated by Kahila rebels for being the heir-apparent in a strong Fatunik-sympathizing Mobal Beshqi tribe.  

His family was instrumental in the development of the Beshquan Turn in Fatunik orthodoxy, which led to the declaration of the Bishopric centered in Beshquohuk, which took power away from the High Council in Eibar.  Nevertheless, their local version of Fatunik theology differs considerably from the `reformed` orthodoxy of the modern Center. 

Internal Conflicts
His multiple love affairs and relationships make his personal life complicated.  Some of his great loves were tragic, losing partners to battles or disease.  In other cases, they were strange and hard to fathom. His encounters with representatives from the Agency, who seemed to appear and disappear like the wind, marked several of his most memorable relationships.

In other cases, he was romantically attracted to other men who didn’t necessarily feel so strongly, suffering from unrequited love. In some case they didn’t have a desire for a same-sex relationship at all.

His multiple off-spring from multiple relationships put the lie to his avowed Fatunikism, as several of them exhibit obviously mixten phenotypes.   There is an expectation that his role as something like sheik of all the Mobal Beshqi would pass to one of his kids via a fair selection process. But he is leery of visiting this heavy responsibility on his kin.

External Conflicts
Has some serious conflicts going on with less-savory bitamin and romperi groups centered in the Kahilakol.  One of his offspring has been missing for some time. He suspects that Xavi has been abducted by the bandits, but isn’t sure. Fundamentalist forces are developing in the central woods around Stanbuk. They are preparing Arguments declaring that the Mobal Beshqi form of Sun-worship is heretical.  This is completely wrapped-up-in and inter-related with the trials being endured by Stanley Phoenix Quinn, who is a kind of adopted second cousin to Mikel Moballeq.

Notes
Although he is a wealthy and influential and respectable personage, Mikel was a member of revolutionary Mobal Beshqi sect as a youth.  This is why he never talks about that period of his life.  Still has fond feelings for alternative approaches to Tomorrow.

Probably need to show a family tree. And outline in more detail the background of the Fatunik internal conflicts and schisms.

