Season


Unique Features
Only one well-kept road through the region, it directly connects Eelan to Bordakol in the Borda Woods and through a much more circuitous route to Mabhakol in Oknott. A smaller, more difficult road connects Eelan to Qurol, just inside the Ring and on the Northern River.  These are mainly commercial connections. Eelaners seldom leave the region.

Description
The region is loosely allied to the Riders Council. It is the most autonomous of the four members of the Federation. In some matters, the Eelani do business directly with the Heliops rather than through Borded.  The folk-religion involves a strong interest in ancient artifacts, but without any hidden meaning, just a kind of ecstatic belief in redemption-from-toil and talismans against re-emergence of catastrophe. Americans might read it as a kind of Baptist faith, de-centralized, congregational, anti-hierarchical. Has some aspects of saint/guru practice also in the manner of Sufis, Sikhs and some Hindus.

