            <Title>Beest, Fon, Rep, and Ixh</Title>
            <Text>Beest, Fon, Rep, and Ixh
Age • Location

Role in Story
-beest is a non-sentient animal, usually but not exclusively mammal, that is used as a means of conveyance.  A mechanical conveyance is a bexobeest.

Fon, -fon, fonda- and similar sounding terms refer to any non-enhanced-sentient animal, especially but not only mammals.   

Rep/Rip/Reep, -rip, -rep, -reep, etc. refers to non-sentient reptiles and amphibians of all types, including snakes, turtles and tortoises. 

Ixh-, -ixh refers to any type of non-sentient creature that swims in the sea, lakes or rivers. 

For example, terms like ursafon or fondabear  describe a bear that doesn't have any enhanced capabilities. Sometimes a bear is just a bear.

There are also plenty of non-sentient worms, ants, centipedes, millipede and other (non-flying) insects and spiders. 

However, bees, butterflies, mosquitos, moths, flies, wasps and hornets are extinct in the Enclosure, which is why there are so many devotees of the Dauni Vakasaqua and other farmers who spend time pollinating plants and distributing seeds by hand.  &lt;— This sis a key focus of describing the Southern lifestyle and crucial to survival of organic life forms in the Saskan Lands.
