The last great battle between Borded and the Heliops was resolved when the Great Wall of Fire was ignited to keep the Fatunik fighters in the Borda Woods from entering the Eelani Hills.  Mount Eelan still looks down on the forest from across the Ring Road, where it is given various fiery nicknames by the Bordans in their tales and songs. The Ring Road between Qurol and Barbol marks roughly the line of the Great Fire, with some physical impacts of the devastation still apparent on both sides a few centuries later.
