            <Title>Hádika</Title>
            <Text>Hádika
Northeastern corner of Norgyte, northernmost tip of Salotriza, on the Ilyushan border

Role in Story


Related Characters


Season


Unique Features


Description

The town of Hádika (or Hadakik depending on your dialect) sits on the border with Wesshewen, near the western foothills of the Ilyushan Mountains.  Its holdings are all on its southern side of the town. There is no opening in the town's walls towards the north or the east. 

The town’s only gate, to south, sits on the Mixry Road, which is the border between Norgyte and Salotriza.  

Hádika is very much a military town and part of the martial traditions and lore of both Norgyte and Salotriza, though in the popular imagination it is probably more closely associated with the Songs of Service and the Obligation of a Volunteer, a song cycle and a long solo vocal piece, respectively, honoring the Volunteers.  

It has a long history as a front-line defense against raiders from the north and monsters from the east.  The Chief of the Watch is the undisputed and leading Fatunik official here.  With its large Fatune Tagabant and two permanent barracks for Volunteers as well, there is a disciplined military aspect to most activities in the town.  The Riders have a significant military presence her, where they collaborate closely with the Fatunik militias. 

The dominant guild alliance in Hádika is The Candle-makers Craft Hall, commonly referred to in the militant anthems that tend to make up the the jaunty Bardsongs of the Northern Gate as “The Three Lights”.  Including the Fatunik Armorers and Cobblers, and the Fatunik Carpenters Guild along with the Candlemakers guild, the Hádika Craft Hall is an effective military supply organization. It produces high-end, heavy-duty metal armor such as chain- and ring-mail, all types of leathery and bony things, along with exquisite short swords and knives.  The continuous demand from both the Heliops and Borded for military equipment guarantees that such guild business thrive here. 

Hádika is not a closed town.  The  trade carried on by the Hádika Candle-makers Craft Hall is conducted with partners from all around the Ring. Hádika hosts one of the best-known and best-supplied arms bazaars in the Saskan Lands.   
