            <Text>Terpinol
Also see Setting Sketch

Type of Location

Terpinol is the only province of the Saskan Lands that might be considered to be a city-state.  The province is properly called the Terpinol Community and unlike the other much larger Southern Lands, it has a formal governance structure. 

Terpinol Toon occupies much of its land area.

The province has the smallest land-area by far of any of the provinces, encompassing only a number of villages and farms in the immediate vicinity of Terpinol Toon, most notably the village of Scatterling, where several "Free and Independent" guilds, as well as a semi-secret society called The Greens, have their headquarters.
Role in Story

Primary Language

Secondary Languages

Demographic Summary

Historical Summary

Physical Description

Terpinol Toon has two main features:

A vast complex called the Star Gazers Academy, which serves as a kind of university as well as an observatory.

A marina serving sea-farers and explorers via the Aran Sea. 

Widely respected throughout the Southern Lands, the Weir Lands and those in the Outer Lands who coalesce their efforts via the Night Hall as a source of learning and engineering, the Academy -- in some subtle ways -- provides the fourth pillar of culture in Saskantinon, balancing the more martial attitudes of Borded, Beshquohuk and High Weir with a deep commitment to critical scientific  thinking and to magical practices.
