            <Title>Lohrn</Title>
            <Text>Lohrn the Carpenter
24 • Ríkila

Role in Story
Has a unique perspective on the foreign lands to the west, beyond the Weir Lands and the Krunkinotto. 

Knowledgable about the internal workings of an important Guild organization.

Let's completely change this character to become a member of Tonedo'a inner circle. I like the background of abuse and so on. But let's make him into a baddie, a real baddie -- the Bannon to Tonedo's Trump, the Goebbels to Tonedo's Hitler.  He becomes a hard core "old believer", breaking with Tonedo when Lohrn starts to believe he is not being "tough enough" with the dissidents.

Goal
Lohrn, for anyone who bothers to ask, likes to provide a commoner’s everyday view of the infamous past events in Ríkila and the current dramas unfolding in the Saskan Lands.  Someone who just wants to get thru the day without too much trouble, isn’t interested in joining any factions. 

Physical Description
Small, often dissheveled due to constant hard working and tendency towards intoxicants. Has a foreign accent reflecting his origins in the (unnamed) western lands beyond the mountains. Does not have a partner and is not in a position of authority, so sexual/gender identity remains neutral/unclear in public settings, at least when there are Tagabants about.  

Personality
Smart. Observant. Quiet.  Tends to focus on practical matters, has an engineer’s eye for things.

Occupation
Is apprenticed to a member of the Carpenter’s Council (c.f. Otto Trucent).

Habits/Mannerisms
Quiet, somewhat fearful. Occasional bouts of drunkeness or intoxication. May be an addict. Has been traumatized and is reluctant to trust anyone. Years in care of Riders/Carpenters brought about better socialization, but has not addressed deeper scars.  

Background
An orphaned refugee from the far west, beyond the Krunkinotto. Home village was ravaged by Entropics (wild bands of marauders, common in Wesshewen, but also further west, where they are even wilder), who enslaved Lohrn as a child. Escaped during a conflict with a Cloned (Jexan) outpost in the mountains, headed south eventually taking a raft downriver into Oknott. Learned to speak Eibar in Borded.  Was put into care of independent Brooders tied to the Carpenters Guild. After hearing the background story during a visit to the brood house, Otto Trucent requested Lohrn as apprentice and then had hir relocated to Ríkila.  

Internal Conflicts
Many psychological scars. Abuse by Entropics left alot of unresolved anger, which Lohrn keeps bottled up.

External Conflicts
Somewhat sympathetic towards the Jaxen due to their role in freeing Lohrn from enslavement, an attitude that is typically very unpopular in the Saskan Lands, gets Lohrn into trouble from time to time. Deepening reliance on intoxicants is drawing Lohrn into unsavory (literally) underworld connections. 

Story-lines
Lohrn's sympathy for the Jaxen struck a chord with Remanj Jexan during one of his trips to Ríkila.




