        <Document ID="F574D74E-E7F8-4189-AEEE-00D249D1F3AF">
            <Title>Powers</Title>
            <Text>I want to avoid a straight Gamma World or superhero or mutant type of storyline.  If this were to become a comic book, it would be situated in a different kind of genre.

This is a science-fiction story more so than a D&amp;D/fantasy world one. Any powers need to have some kind of explanation, even if the physics of it is questionable.

Nevertheless, there are elements of supra-huum capabilities arising in some cases. This can easily be conflated with magical or other influences and so on, as well as theories about the Agency's influence. The origins of the powers can reside in the more-or-less typical comic book explanations... tied into the overall DNA-mixing theme in a meaningful way, hopefully, along with some engineering of ET and terrestrial origins.  Some powers come from technological enhancements rather than biological origins.  

With the killer bugs, a wee nod to Starship Troopers, but also tied into the incompetence of the overlords. The arrival of the bugs within the Enclosure is an accident, not part of the zookeepers’ plans.

Likewise, the re-emergence of birds should present a different perspective on powers, as well as on evolution. What if things are re-booted on an avian rather than mammalian basis? What types of powers would be considered extraordinary then?

If possible, without getting too worked up about or too literal about it, would like any powers to tie to some specific origin and not just be explained away as 'magic'. Please no werewolves, zombies or vampires.  Though we will have shadowy 'monsters'. 

Categories of powers

Strength
	◆	Large muscle mass
	◆	Excellent muscle control
	◆	Rapid attack

Speed
	◆	Short bursts of high speed

Aromas
	◆	Attraction odor
	◆	Repellent odor

Bites/Injections/Poisons
	◆	Paralyzing
	◆	Deadly

 Other? 

Use the Saskan Schema software to inventory, describe, categorize powers. Then pick a few that help drive the story.


</Text>
