        <Document ID="E09C608D-D6C8-431F-A5B7-86858D6C74BE">
            <Title>Monmar Massachawa</Title>
            <Text>Monmar Massachawa
32 • Somewhere in the High Weir Lands

Role in Story
A bandit leader who is proud of the independent culture of the High Weir Lands, distinct from -- though not opposed to -- the Empafarasi legacy there. 

A fallen angel. The dark force. An enigma. The anima.
Goal
Monmar is a strong female leader who is neither overly sexualized nor gender-neutralized.  Her connection to story-lines regarding flight -- she is another one of the bird-related characters -- brings the Agency's know-how into the picture.  

Physical Description
Tall, strong, lithe.  Has woodpecker DNA, which gives her a strong not-to-be-fucked-with natural punk rock look. Openly female but not femme.  Demands respect. Is a leader and considers herself elite.

Personality
Commanding.  Intelligent.  Does not like to be trifled with. Does not suffer fools gladly. 

Occupation
Trained as an astro-pilot by the Agency, then returned to the Saskan Lands to assist in the development of the Empafarasi, mainly in order to counter the aggression of the Jaxen.  Ostensibly she leads a very clever bitamin gang located in the mountains north of High Weir called the Circle of Fives.

These are interlocking cells of agents, each actually with 7 members, who communicate in a systematic way via the member of each cell designated as the Dominant Seventh.  In Saskan terms, this resonates as something of an argumentative take on  Scarcity and Plenty, with its philosophical emphasis on Sixes plus a Gap.

MM, as she is sometimes referred to, was instrumental in organizing a number of the actions that led up to the Event in Ríkila and led to the astonishing arrival of the Empafarasi Riders that turned the battle for the Toon in favor of the Moonic forces. 
Habits/Mannerisms
A technical whiz, given her natural capacities and her Agency training. Has introduced numerous contraptions for use by the Circle. Careful to hide the connection to the Agency, even from her colleagues in High Weir.  
A consummate leader, she is always planning the next caper and thinking several moves ahead of her competitors and opponents. Abjures having a large public presence. Is willing to take the same types of risks she expects from members of her network.

Background
Wanted by both Fatunik and Rider Authorities for numerous crimes, including piracy, grand larceny, unsanctioned trade, tax evasion, kidnapping, terrorism, murder, espionage, having incorrect and heretical thoughts, parasitism,  and the illegal propagation of proscribed song cycles.

On her record at the Agency she is red-flagged for unlicensed operation of a deep space vehicle, attempted manipulation of the time line, and improper handling of wormhole gravitons.  She  also has commendations for expert piloting, expert marksmanship, and advanced understanding of inter-universal atonal vibrational dynamics at meta-quantum manifold frequencies. 

She is very fond of many kinds of music and insists that members of the Circle learn multiple song cycles as well as some aspects of music theory.

Internal Conflicts
In her younger days, had an on-again, off-again affair with the other MM, Mikel Moballeq. At one point it seemed that would develop into a long-term partnership, something that she was about to propose to MM, at which point Mikel and Azron Gurk got involved in a long, complicated philosophical discussion that lasted for four days. During this time, Jesse K contacted Monmar and laid out the first set of proposed guidelines for the Circle of Fives.  This led to… well, a lot of work.  Monmar never found the time to return to MM with her proposal.  She sometimes struggles with this decision, and occasionally yearns for a more peaceful life she could share with a partner who is her equal and with whom she might be able to share her whole story.  She is kind of lonely. 

External Conflicts
Many.  With the Jaxen, she is in constant combat. With the Heliops, she is a major threat.  With the Riders, she threatens their monopolies.  With the Dauni Vakasaqua of Low Weir and the Legalists of The Runes of Bye, she is too much of a trouble-maker, too radical.  With Kahila and other bitamin and romperi outfits, she is competition. With the Agency, she is difficult if not impossible to control and often goes off the radar as well.  With the Empafarasi of High Weir, she must deal with a lot of stupidity and egoism from folks who are nowhere near her equal. 

