MM's team makes it to Beshquohuk where they attempt unsuccessfully to rescue Iohane and Henqu.

Following the omen that appeared in the Deep Pool in Juuj, and Iohane's defiant singing of Birakay's song, a popular rising erupts in Beshquohuk.

Reports pour in (to whom?) regarding varied protests, both peaceful and violent, against the sacrifice of the Two Riders, about the vile murder of a Candlemaker, of sightings of the terrorist gang led by Monmar Massachawa, of stirrings among the Kahila and the Nye-folk, of mobilizations among the Empafarasi, and even of Volunteers and Garda abandoning their duties. 

