SPQ's real "crime" is being a "criminal philosopher", particularly with respect to choosing to ignore the nationalism, racialism, speciesism and particularist genealogy of popular authority and focusing his attention instead on the here and now, on observable facts, and on valuing the particular dignity and intelligence of dignified, intelligent entities over the "common historical knowledge" espoused by popular and established mouthpieces of statist authority.







