        <Document ID="E4576CEB-0297-4733-B5FB-7FE4595D6824">
            <Title>Remanj Jexan</Title>
            <Text>Remanj Jexan
20 • village of Unnaghobik in Salotriza, off the road between Mixry and Hádika

Role in Story
Perspective of a poor farmer's family caught up in the winds of war.
A Jaxen who evolves.  The puppet who came to life.
The surname Jexan is a title adopted by members of the Returner sect that he belongs to.  
Goal
Remanj feels all the suffering of the age. He is not invested in any of the existing ideological solutions.  Is not particularly fond of music, but it sometimes captures his attention when it is absolute (non-lyrical).

Physical Description
Long curly red hair. Silver eyes. Handsome in a shy way.

Personality
Sometimes perceived as sneaky and deceptive, the result of his difficult upbringing, fears regarding his parents' disappearance and his odd personality traits, which are due to the fact that he is actually Jaxen, but has been evolving biological traits, including emotional life and independent consciousness separate from the hive.

He does not realize he is machinic. Thinks that the "voices in his head" are dreams and whatnot. Believes that his parents were huum.

Powers
Mild empathetic sort of telepathy -- can detect fear, anxiety, lying and their opposites if he can look a person in the eyes. Likely the result of experimentation carried out on him by one of his now-disappeared huum "parents". 


Occupation
Apprenticed to a small but reknowned "Downer" (psychiatric/psychological care) unit in his village serving mainly Fatunik and Rider military units stationed in the region, particularly those returning from the northern and eastern borderlands.  The unit is led by legendary scanner Rollo of the Dexelites.

Member of a small local Returner cult called the Nightingales.  Their banner is a Red Bird on a white background. 

Occasionally gathers info on commission from the Scanners Detecting Agency of Two Trees, sometimes looking for infiltrators from Ilyushan, but more often a less dire nature.
Habits/Mannerisms
Can read and write proper Eibar. Speaks with a lilting Salotrizan accent. 
Knows some Eibarq and can understand Sogomsh.
Most prized possession is a drawing of his natural parents, who vanished when he was 12.
His closest companion is a natural (non-enhanced-sentience) dog named Fluke.
Skilled at knife-throwing.

Background
Was a Jaxen surreptitiously taken from an inn in Pavanarune Toon.  His "parents" were a rogue agent and a Mobalbesq scientist of sorts who thought they had found a method to make the Jaxen into huum.  Their work on Remanj was their only experiment before they were abducted by the Watch.  They are currently in a tightly-controlled sequestration village outside of Mixry.

Remanj is unaware of his past outside of Unnaghobik, but has a facility for language, along with his empathic powers, that far exceeds anything known in the village. Through his travels, he connected with Rollo of the Dexellites, and works with him as a kind of healer, particularly on the diagnostic side.

His two brothers, Novarick (younger) and Nabalon (older), are both poor farmers in the village eking out a living on the landhold left by their parents. Remanj has traveled on the Ring and encountered a number of characters in the story, several of whom have developed an attraction to him.
Internal Conflicts
Nabalon accused Remanj of being responsible for their natural parents' disappearance, a false accusation that still hurts.

External Conflicts
Drawn into adventuring by wanderers from the Weir Lands when he was 14-ish, Remanj has been around the Ring and has traveled all the way to High Weir and back. He is aware, to some degree of the great conflict that is about to erupt in the eastern lands.  He is anxious to set up a new operation closer to the front, where there are sure to be plenty of troubled clients, but Rollo is not sure Remanj is ready for that. 

The relationship between the 3 siblings, already troubled, suffers because Remanj is often away, not helping with their small farmland.  

Story-lines
