        <Document ID="67B05C3C-17F2-4DBA-9F2B-017F9680929B">
            <Title>Waleran Tanaraka</Title>
            <Text>Waleran Tanaraka 
32 seasons • from the Barbarana

Role in Story
A guide and story-teller. A cohort of B'arqo and other key players. Provides the perspective of a traditional Settan astrologer with deep knowledge of the southern traditions and languages.

Wizardly in a geeky sort of way.  Has a connection, even if he is unaware of it, to the Agency.
Goal
Provide the Settan perspective and bring the traditionalist, non-Kahila southerners into the story.

Get a deeper dive into the musical/bard traditions of the lands.

Physical Description
Tall, angular.  Always seems to be reading something, consulting charts/manuals, etc.  Practices various forms of moving meditation and martial arts.
Personality
Verbose, a stereotype of an overly educated fool. Has a very high opinion of self and like-minded or seemingly like-minded folk.  Nevertheless, is entirely capable of helping in a fight, especially through the use of mildly advanced technology and weapons, as well as advanced fighting techniques. 
Occupation
Has elementary knowledge of astronomy and mathematics. But it is warped by his strong belief in astrology and a system of fortune-telling that combines astronomical observations with calculations and chanting/meditation. Well-known especially for facility in divining the meaning of “falling stars” and “fast wanderers”. (Which we will eventually find out are mostly spaceships and satellites moving around in the outer atmosphere.)

Habits/Mannerisms
Fond of Terrapina culture. Vegetarian.  Intensely interested in written materials. Has been seeking an audience with Ramona.  Expert in the southern languages, including Doremah.  Fond of music and song but not a talented singer or player himself. A strong sponsor/fan of those who are, c.f. Barakay and Luvcando.
Background
Originally from the wide-open and somewhat wild lands of Barbarana. Considers Terpinol home. Has been to the Land of the Komikol at least once. Has sailed on the Aran Sea and visited Aranzen. Is well-travelled.  Devout member of a Settan River-Soul cult, but -- rather unusually -- is also a leading member of the Star Gazers Academy of Terpinol, specializing in theological analysis of the stars.  Is clueless as to the true nature of the Enclosure, but has a fascinating grasp of the metaphysics of it. 
Internal Conflicts
Deeply cynical despite an up-beat personality. Does not trust/is not satisfied with any of the main or secondary powers, including the Empafarasi, the Eelan, the Seff (octo-folk) and so on.  Has a nagging feeling that nobody really knows what is really going on and he is pretty much right about that.   A pacifist at heart, Waleran is conflicted about having to support / work with militants like Mur’ray and others.
External Conflicts
One of the players being actively monitored by an Agent, Waleran occasionally gets an  external assist in a divination in order to achieve a desired outcome sought by an Agent.  This can contradict establishing stargazing algorithms, which forces Waleran to start to develop a more scientific outlook — which is fundamentally at odds with both Settan and Star-Gazer theologies. 
As a well-known Stargazer, Waleran is pre-sanctioned by the Heliocastron and has to be careful when traveling in the inner Northern areas. 
Story-lines
An aide, ally and old friend to B'arqo. 
</Text>
