        <Document ID="6992FC1E-98EB-4B54-BD78-B87944905C63">
            <Title>Giltraq</Title>
            <Text>Giltraq
26 • Mixry

Role in Story
Member of the Front Tagabant who tries, against the odds, to keep some kind of order in Mixry.
Flees to Ríkila after witnessing the execution of Iohane and Henqu and getting swept up in the uprising. 

In Ríkila, he gets a job cleaning up at the Twelve Moons, where he is housed in one of the small hovels for workers behind the Inn. 

Still ideologically loyal to the Fatunik creeds, but his trust in the Center is shaken. Is taken aback at first by the lack of modesty, willingness to perform genders in the free town.  Discovers that he is more attracted to women than to men. Has trouble explaining why he is in the "starry" side of Ríkila, doesn't have a good cover story, but doesn't want to attract attention. 

He ends up unintentionally betraying the location of on Outerlander resistance camp to the Tagabant. This results in the death of Showan Nywing, who was visiting the camp trying to convince the Kahila and others to take a peaceful path to resistance. His death sparks the Byenung to increase their opposition to the Center and move towards armed resistance.

Shocked by all that, he doubles down on his Fatunik faith, organizes a Volunteer militia that is instrumental in the defense of Ingar and is acclaimed the new Head of the Council of the Eibarfolk after the fall of the Beshquohuk regime.
Goal
Wants to present the Fatunik mission in a benign context -- protecting civilization against chaos -- despite its rather obvious shortcomings.

Physical Description
Huum.  A bro. Big heart.   

Personality
Empathetic.  Not the sharpest knife in the drawer, and has difficulty accepting new or complex concepts. But willing to listen and learn.

Occupation
Guard on the run. Janitor.

