            <Title>Malavorra</Title>
            <Text>Malavorra
Unknown • Low Weir

Role in Story
The living, breathing personification of the River-Soul of Settan tradition.  A warrior queen  of giant size, even those who don't hold to the Southern beliefs consider her to be something like a force of nature. A guru, a totem, a living legend.

Referred to as the Jexan Mother by a sub-group Jexan Returners.  Holds various honorifics in the southern Lands.

Goal
To strengthen the role of women, girls, female gender in the Saskan Lands.
To deepen the knowledge and influence of the Dauni Vakasaqua. Bring the stories of the River-Soul into more lives, emphasizing the critical importance of having deep spiritual ties to the land, the earth, the waters in order to prevent catastrophe. 
Physical Description
Very tall, very big, very curvy. Expressively feminine appearance. Combative when necessary.
Some raven DNA.  Speaks all the languages of the region, including those known in Aranzen and Wesshewen with great facility.
 
Personality
Falstaffian. Fond of s’lah, of which she is a provider of a potent herbal blend. 
Has had multiple lovers and many children. Gets along fine with huum but is especially fond of sints.

Occupation
One of the leading personalities of Low Weir's mostly matriarchal society, Malavorra is an important political figure in the western lands. Along with having a near-divine status in the eyes of many, she is also well-known throughout the southern lands as a tireless and pragmatic coordinator of free and independent Dauni Vakasaqua collectives. The free southern Dauni Vakasaqua are a self-governing member organization, a federation à la Mondragon.

Habits/Mannerisms
Handles a wide variety of concerns relating to Low Weir, her large extended family, her friends and lovers, the broader political and military situations, and the business of the Dauni Vakasaqua collectives.  Works hard.  Plays hard.  Travels a great deal.  Makes a big impression anywhere she goes.  Not subtle.  A strong but fair negotiator.  Has numerous gifts of healing as part of her Dauni Vakasaqua kit.

Background
Nobody knows how old Malavorra is or how she came to be. Many simply regard her as a goddess. Legends, songs about her abound.  Folks can be surprised when they actually meet her, having assumed the tales about her are fanciful. She herself has little recollection of how she came to be. 

It is a dream-like memory of emerging, coalescing out of chaos, growing and evolving with a wide variety of huum and animal influences. She is often drawn to the river and participates in many of the popular ancient Settan rituals. She ages very, very slowly but is not Terrapina. 

 She was created as part of multiple Agency interventions several centuries ago.  She doesn’t know this and the Agency records on it have been obscured, tampered with, and damaged.

Internal Conflicts
Being long-lived brings its own kind of suffering. She has seen many of her acquaintances, friends, lovers and children pass away. She feels the pain behind the Catastrophe like a personal event. Though she disagrees with their cosmology, their politics, and their gender culture, she appreciates the concern that Heliops have about preventing its recurrence. 

External Conflicts
Some factions within the Heliocastronic Center see her as a threat due to her enormous popularity, not only in the western and southern lands, and amongst females in particular.  They spread counter-propaganda aimed at smearing her reputation. 

Notes
Likely interesting to have flashbacks based on Malavorra's dreams and recollections.  

Story lines





