            <Title>Actors and Bards</Title>
            <Text>Actors and Bards
Type • Main Locations

Role in Story
Much of the culture of the Saskan Lands is embedded in song cycles particular to the regions. Bards are the cultural ambassadors, preserving tradition and knowledge, passing it along, and providing entertainment and a certain amount of indoctrination and philosophy for the masses. 

