        <Document ID="07C31150-041E-42B2-8A75-2D4E4569041F">
            <Title>APPENDIX</Title>
            <Text>APPENDIX

Words listed in bold italics approximate their pronunciation in Eibar and Sogomsh, respectively.  Words listed in bold are shown in the language used in this report.


Bar, Ber
The major languages of the Saskan region — Eibar, Eibarq, Sogomsh, Arqa and Arqq — are in the Bar family of languages.  The Bar language family also includes three minor languages:  Ahbar, Eibeerq, and Sleebar. Eibar, Eibarq and Sogomsh are mutually intelligible to a large degree. The others somewhat less so in comparison.  Eibar is considered to be the Ur bar language from which the others evolved.

beest
Almost always used as a suffix.  A -beest is any non-sentient animal, usually mammal, used as a means of conveyance.  Mechanical conveyances are referred to as a bexobeest.

Eibar, Eber
Eibar is the most pervasive language of the huum population, spoken by virtually all huum residents of Saskantinon, as well as most others sints north of the Settan River.

Eibar is the language of power in the Saskan region. It is the official language of the two major huum-centric political federations -- the Borded Federation, and the federated and associated provinces of the Fatunikan Dominion. It is the canonical language of the Noonday Scribes of Fatunika, who exert a strong ideological presence.  

In the the Kahila lands and in the Runes of Bye, provinces which are only loosely associated with the Fatunikan Dominion, Eibar is widely understood and used but Sogomsh is more pervasive in daily usage. The Magisters of Byenung are renowned for their expertise with spoken and written Eibar. 

The pronunciation of Eibar as it is spoken in the province of Eibar is considered to be the oldest and hence most "proper" spoken form. Eibar province, near the mouth of the Pavan River, was the earliest settlement of Bar-speaking huum in the region adhering closely to the Fatunikan dogma.  As the centuries passed, the Eibar language diversified as the huum population spread and immigrants arrived from Wesshewen, Ilyushan, Krbshanana, Aranzen and other lands even further away.  Along with multiple Bar languages, a wide variety of local Eibar accents, in some cases verging on dialects, developed as well. 

"Old Eibar", as the "proper" form is called, is particularly characteristic of three important organizations: the Noonday Scribes, the Byenung Magisters and the Council of the Eibarfolk.

All Eibar-speaking areas of Saskantinon sport regional accents.  In most cases they consist of minor variations in vowel sounds and a few idiomatic words. Those closest to being full-fledged dialects are spoken in the western provinces, especially in the remote hills and valleys of Eelan and the High Weir Lands, and in the remote northern plains of Oaknott, Norgyte and Sungyte.

Endor, Ander
Largest of 6 tidally locked moon-satellites of Gavor-Havorra.  Also refers to night-time hours generally, especially to nights bright with moonlight.  Used in naming a variety of moons-centered ideologies/theologies/belief systems.  

Fatune, Vaton
Sun/star at the center of the Gavoran solar system.  Also refers to daylight hours generally.  Root name of major huum political federation in Saskantinon, the Fatunikan Dominion. Used in name of the major sun-centered theology/ideology/belief-system.

fon, von
Fon, -fon, fonda- and similar prefixes and suffixes refer to any non-enhanced, non-sint animal, especially but not only mammals.  For example, an animal with 100% bear DNA might be referred to as a bearfon or a vondabear.

huum
Sentient beings with human phenotype (appearance) and who are presumed to have completely human, or almost completely human, genotype (genetic material) as well.

Gavor, Ghav
For those who understand the nature of the planet's astro-geography, Gavor/Ghav is the name of the planet, that is, of the entire world. Commonly used to indicate all land, seen or unseen, whether planetary astro-geography is understood or not.  In other words, all places that are not ocean. The world name is often rendered as Gavor-Havorra or Ghav-Avorr, indicating all the lands and seas. When used in an astro-cosmological sense, then just Gavor/Ghav or Gavoran/Ghavan is more typical. (Also see Havorra)

Havorra, Avorr
The world-ocean. All salt water bodies everywhere, whether the nature of the planet is fully understood or not. The world name is often rendered as Gavor-Havorra or Ghav-Avorr, meaning all the land and all the seas.  (Also see Gavor)

ixh, ikth
Ixh-, -ixh or Ikth-, -ikth refer to any type of non-sint creature that is neither mammal (fon) nor rip, and swims in the sea, lakes or rivers. 

Lurabar, Lorrber
Continent which contains the Saskan Lands and its neighboring regions.

rip, rep
Rep, Rip, Reep, -rip, -rep, -reep, etc. refer to non-sint reptiles and amphibians of all types, including snakes, lizards, turtles and tortoises. 

Sella, Zell
Second-largest of the 6 tidally locked moon-satellites of Gavor-Havorra. Used in naming a variety of moons-centered belief systems, particularly those combining river-centric concepts relating to the Settan.

Settan
The southern of two major river systems in Saskantinon. With its main source in the high mountains to the west of the Weir Lands, the Settan runs through the entire Saskan Lands from west to east, with many small tributaries feeding into it. The Settan fills the Great Bye Lake, then continues through its natural course to the Krbsh Sea. Saskan provinces south of the Settan are called the Settan Lands, where the river is the object of veneration for many river-centered ideologies/theologies/belief systems widespread in those provinces.

sint
Sentient beings with non-human phenotype, who obviously have some non-human DNA mixed into their genotype.

Sints vary a great deal in appearance. Some have very human-like features with only a few minor characteristics of their non-huum DNA apparent. Others are very distinctly non-human. Due to the modifications made and significant amounts of human DNA used to adapt brain size, larynx and, often, coding of extremities to develop fine motor skills, it is very unusual for sints to be indistinguishable or largely indistinguishable from  their non-sentient ancestors. (Also see beest, fon, rip, and ixh)

Untamed
The term "Untamed" was originally used pejoratively by huum opposed to viewing sints as equals. It was intended to cast sints as Other, wild, violent, dangerous and so on. Over the centuries, it was adopted by sints themselves as an ironic label and now carries little emotional weight; it just means "a sint organization".  (Also see: sint)

Within the Saskan Lands are a wide variety of sint organizations, often organized along species lines.  They vary in purpose.  Most practice self-defense, community mutual aid, dialogue and cooperation with huum or with other sint communities, promote training and education, and so on.  Others are more radical, some revolutionary, a few are violently anti-huum. These political groups follow a bewildering brew of ideologies.   





</Text>
