Nobody and nothing flies in the Saskan Lands. Azron Gurk, a wizardly-character, intervened to prevent SPQ from thinking too much about flight, creating a mystery about who that character is --while literally bringing Icarus down to earth.  


As the tales wind down, Jax Remanj, the waiter from the first chapter, acts up, throwing a kind of zen wrench into the idea that we thought we understood everything.  So this chapter ends on a discordant  tritone. Not a recognizable song cycle. 



