            <Text>Lots of strong, interesting characters are being defined, which is great. Continue to develop each one of them.


Do  more to align each one to a story arc, to categorize, to balance...

- Assemble a cross reference or a graph of Acts/Chapters/Scenes where each character appears. Who are really the main characters based on that?

- How many male/female/other, gay/straight/other, good/bad/ambiguous characters are there?  Old/young/middle aged?  Children?  How many huum vs. sint vs. Machinic vs. biologic vs. extraterrestrial? 

- I have studiously ignored racial characteristics of the huum characters. Is that workable? Does anything need to be said about their appearance?

- Are any of the names jarringly out of place? 
