        <Document ID="2A860AD8-7CB6-481A-99C3-6914F5CDE205">
            <Title>Ingar</Title>
            <Text>Ingar
Largest town in Eibar province, near the confluence of the Pavan and Rocking Rivers

Role in Story
One of the oldest towns. Close to the eastern border and the Krbsh Sea. Get a taste of travelers from afar.

Related Characters
A number of characters who play a role in the Saskan Lands but come from outside of it arrive via Ingar. May also be a place where defectors, escapees go to — who are considering emigration. 

Season
Typically humid. 

Unique Features
Something of a safe haven for inbound and outbound refugees. Since it is so foundational to Eibarian culture and language, it is difficult for fundamentalist Sun worship to get a foothold. Think of its relation to mainstream Beshquohukian Heliocastronism as something like that of Iran prior to the mullah regime and/or maybe Turkey to the Sunni-Arab-Islamic world. Yes, we are believers, but with our own rich history and traditions thank you very much.  

Description

While not one of the largest towns, it has a lot of traffic, with three roads in and out and close to two major bends in the river. Also close to the border with Ilyushan. It is one of the few towns that has villages packed around it for some distance, rather than just rural villages and farms. 
Sights
The Great Holly Temple, featuring a gigantic drooping holly tree at its center, is an ancient elaborate structure that has been built up and around the tree for generations.  It is officially a Fatunik place of worship but the upper floors were appropriated by the High Council of the Eibarfolk many years ago.  

This is a language academy devoted to collecting information about Eibar accents, dialects and so on.  It does not try to enforce a proper Eibar.  On its uppermost floors, it is more like a combination trading company / bank / insurance company, sponsoring multiple types of  expeditions on behalf of its board.  

The “High Council” plays an important role in financing (loans, credits, partnerships) throughout the northern and eastern provinces. It works with Kahila enterprises to some extent, but is very wary of romperi influences.  

Active/devout Heliocastronic membership is low as compared to other Fatunik centers. The Fatune Tagabant is active and visible, but mainly deals with ordinary law/order concerns.  The Dorq Tagabant is seldom heard from, dealing mainly with more obscure espionage concerns.  

The Gleaming is not observed in Ingar.  Instead, there is an annual voluntary public Confession in which Sun worshippers process to the River while chanting mournfully and punching each other in the arm. At the river they perform a ritual bathing, to wash away any “moonful and starry excrescence” that has accumulated during the past year. 

There is an Astrologers Laboratory in Ingar, as well as a variety of small, but well-attended Kahila and Settan temples and meeting-houses scattered throughout the town and its surroundings. Though of course Eibar is not a participant in the Night Hall, there is a First Arrivers community hall -- effectively an embassy from the Runes of Bye -- which seeks to build up good relations between Eibar and the other provinces of the Outer Lands.
Sounds
A busy, active place. Lots of coming and going. Lots of commerce. 

Smell
The occasional foul stench emanating from Ilyushan.

Notes

