        <Document ID="83C3C9C7-8F99-4B1B-8E9E-6CADDE5D6E0D">
            <Title>Kam</Title>
            <Text>Kam
29 seasons • Jivákala

Role in Story
A Fatunik believer and worker.
A worker who awakes to class consciousness, with a sense of humor.

A wise fool. Think Charlie Chaplin.
Kam stumbles into most of the situations in which he gets involved, evaluating their meaning only later.

Goal
Tell a story of both assimilation and emerging identity, as well as fear of being outed.  Keep it complex. Kam does not hate the Fatunik community. He loves it, even though he feels estranged from it. 

His story explains the gender expression culture and politics of the Fatunik communities, which is inter-related with its misogynistic class hierarchies.

A transformative agent in a kind of Daoist tradition.  He is part of the network that ends up introducing flying creatures and constructing flying machines, though he'd had no such intention.  

Physical Description
Hefty, solid with especially muscular legs. Having passed the age of presentation, performed a ritual of exposure, and mated, he presents publicly as male without fear or shame. But expects use of male honorifics only with his work gang subordinates, since he is not in a position of leadership &amp; authority in any other context. 
Personality
Plodding but genuine and big-hearted

Occupation
Carpenter’s gang lead. 

Habits/Mannerisms


Background
Released by his biological parents to a Fatunik brooder house near Khaliro as an infant, Kam was raised in the pre-Beshquain. Juuj-and-Eibar-centered Fatunik tradition.  Although he seemed destined for the Tagabant due to his size and strength, a Traveling Sister of the Way of All Things convinced the brooders to direct him into the Fatunik Carpenters Guild instead.  Once he finished his apprenticeship, the Guild sent him to Jivákala where he works mainly constructing ready-made materials for Volunteer Camps. 

He is the parent of two broodlings resident in Jivákala.

Internal Conflicts
He has some oxen DNA, of which he is aware, though not sure of the details. He has covered up this fact his entire life. His feet are slightly cloven.  Conflicted about whether to reveal this to his offspring. Although he participates in Gleaming activities, it is with concern that some day he may be exposed as star-crossed himself.
External Conflicts
He has been visited twice by the Traveling Sisters since they directed him into the Carpenters as a youth. Both times he was given a mission to build a small but relatively complex piece of machinery (related to gliders, it will turn out) for them in secret, which he did.  One of his mates has discovered this side work and the Watch is now keeping a careful eye on Kam.

Notes

Brooder-raised Fatunik children are not given a family name except in cases where it was requested by the natural parents.  Once they are apprenticed, they are typically referred to by the name of their guild or their title, like Kam Carpenter, and sometimes, often in an abbreviated way, by a location they are closely associated with, like Kam Carpenterjivá.

Story lines




