            <Title>Rillbeck the Runner</Title>
            <Text>Rillbeck the Runner
30-ish • Along the banks of the Pavan

Role in Story
A tasty villain of no particular consequence. Rillbeck the Runner is a powered mixed-sint whom puros love to hate.  

Goal
Rillbeck loves to make funny, satirical versions of the heroic stories and songs about Riders, Tagabants and Volunteers.

Physical Description
Enormously obese but very fast. Rillbeck propels himself quickly along the banks of the rivers and over the water by generating both gas and heat from his body. In effect a fart-propulsion system with malodorous consequences. 

He has the ability to launch a fear-generating sonic attack by expertly imitating the sounds of scary things — wild beasts, barbarians, and eerie other-worldly non-harmonic tones. Not to mention the smell, which is also fearful.

He is quite strong, especially when threatened.
Personality
A bully and a thief.  Has rapacious appetites for food. He is a fence as well.

Occupation
Has a burrow along the River Pavan, between Khaliro and Rutónik where he hides out and stashes stuff.  Commands a small guerrilla of like-minded river rats, meaning part-rat sints who thrive along the river. They have no loyalties.

Habits/Mannerisms
Rude. Boisterous. Loud.

Background
Deeply disturbed, Rillbeck is the result of an experiment gone awry. He has no sense of his parentage. His was wiped at an early age before he escaped into the wild. 

Internal Conflicts
Persistent nightmares. Feels abandoned and un-loved.

External Conflicts
Always on the run.  Hunted by both Rider and Heliop authorities. Not looked-upon kindly by Kahila or romperi groups either.  Petty conflicts amongst the rat-troops too.

