        <Document ID="939B7C13-217E-47C0-9491-5914EADEE6DE">
            <Title>Iohane</Title>
            <Text>Iohane
27 • Borded

Role in Story
Iohane seeks to bring harmony to the Ring.  Her attitude is an insight into the life of a Ring Rider. She is a knight. A warrior.  And even a little bit of a true princess. 

Iohane and Henqu die in the Gleaming. They are martyrs. Their suffering unleashes great changes throughout the Lands.

Don’t want to steal too much from Game of Thrones. But killing a 'King' more or less during the Fade In certainly gets the audience’s attention! Using a successful plot twist in a new way is Hollywood-standard.
In this case, set up the audience to think I and H are going to be our heros, but then kill them off, shocking everyone. That helps to reveal that our real hero is SPQ and his cohorts. 

I need to figure out how, where SPQ is on trial, for what heresy. Showan and the Byenung community work on his legal defense.

He is not on trial initially for condemning the killing of Iohane and Henqu, but their death intensifies the case against and for SPQ. 
 
Goal
To hear the silence of a falling star lighting up a purple sky. To show the way. To tie together the old traditions and the new path.
Physical Description
Lanky but physically strong. Female/hetero, un-partnered but in love with Henqu. Like all Ring Riders, outward appearance, presentation is gender neutral but not obsessively so. Usually seen only well-armored and armed. 

Personality
Outspoken in a straightforward likable way. Good at intervening in dicey situations before they get out of hand, using her words to calm down conflicts.  Strong as an ox and twice as deadly when needed.
Sometimes called a weir witch by certain Heliops due to her knowledge of the western lands, but she is not related to any Weir Lands tribes nor is she affiliated with the Empafarasi.

Occupation
Ring Rider.

Habits/Mannerisms
Always correct, as befits a Ring Rider, but willing to crack a joke to ease tensions, or to make a slightly racy or caustic remark in order to get folks’ attention. 

Background
From a hardscrabble farming village in the Norgyte. Most of her clan are battle-hardened, having defended their farms many times from entropic raiders coming down from the Wesshewen plains.  Recruited into the Fatune Tagabant in Mixry after serving a time with the Volunteers, Iohane chose to abandon the Heliop barracks, voluntarily went to Borded when she was 21 to offer her sword to the Riders Council.  

This happened after a chance encounter with a Ring Rider named Henqu, who impressed her immensely, not least of all with his song.  And after meeting Ramona, who opened her heart to the Terrapina, to the river-soul.

Internal Conflicts
Prone to seeing the best in all the traditions and over-looking the worst, Iohane is a natural advocate for unity between beklek and bexik, between Heliops, Kahila, Settan, Arnazen and so on. She has a vast vision of post-Catastrophical unity that even encompasses the entropic tribes and the faraway lands of Shanowa and Ayshewen. The threats posed by the monsters of the Ilyushan Mountains, the mysteries of the Forgh and the Komikol, and the dire possibilities of Re-emergence posed by the Bugs, or whatever they are, in the Krunkinotto, give her pause. She worries that only an apocalyptic conflict with such forces can remove the threat they pose, but she believes there is a higher power that will come the aid of the sentients.

External Conflicts
All the usual problems of being a cop on the Ring, plus some continuing meanness and vulgarity from former comrades in Mixry and the surrounding parts of the Ring where efforts were made to tarnish her reputation after she joined the Riders.

Story lines




