            <Title>Kaharan</Title>
            <Text>Kaharan
Early 20's • Barbol/Heliohlan

Role in Story
Kaharan is a rural Settany person caught up in the machinations of a Heliop town. The mother/father come to visit when Kaharan is being held in Heliohlan. In this encounter a variety of Bordawood Fatunik minor characters are encountered as well.

See the scene: "Death of a candlemaker"
Goal
Kaharan is fond of and knowledgeable about many aspects of the diverse Dauni Vakasaqua communities.  She interweaves love of plants, of friends, of community, of family, and knowledge of gardening into her story-telling.  She is acutely concerned with the dire situation with hunger in the Lands, the critical importance of the pollinators, the desperation that ensues from the Hunger.

A little bit of Gretel from Hansel and Gretel. A rural innocent preyed up by both bad and good 'witches'. 

Physical Description

Dauni Vakasaqua come in many sizes, shapes, forms and have multiple names.  Love of gardening, use of herbs for healing and so on is a practice that crosses over the religious/ideological/genetic divides. There are both Fatunik and Lunik Dauni Vakasaqua, and from other traditions too.  Their knowledge and practices are similar.  They can and do learn from each other, providing an important bridge between the communities, in some ways like the Returner cults, who also cross over the political and ideological divides.

A spiritual and pastoral herbalism is very strong south of the rivers, where it takes on a religious character inter-twined with the Earth-centric/animist beliefs of many residents, and tied together with their understanding of the river-soul, of nature as a living, sentient or nearly-sentient entity, the veneration of Malavorra, and so on. 
Personality
Kaharan's family are from the Settany countryside outside of Barbol Toon, between the Ring and the River Setta.  This is a Sogomsh speaking area where devotions to the River-Soul are widespread.  

Occupation
In the terms used by southerners, she is a Gardener (or Herbalist, but I don't want to use that term) as opposed to a Farmer. This reflects her deeper knowledge of plant life, pollination techniques, and so on. 

Kaharan went across the river looking for a special type of herb thought to grow only in the Borda Woods, in order to treat an illness in the village back home. One thing led to another and it ended up being a trip all the way to Heliohlan —  at the invitation of some kindly Fatunik Dauni Vakasaqua met along the way. An opportunity arose to get a job with higher pay and greater prestige than could be obtained in short time going through the lengthy apprentice process back home. 

One there, things got dicey. 

