            <Title>Returners</Title>
            <Text>Returners
Local cults • All over the place, but especially in the Southwest and Northeast

Role in Story


Relationship to Other Organizations


Description

A widespread cult with many local colors. Basic belief system is that they want to Return to the time before the Catastrophe. 
Dexelites have a syncretic Fatunik-Returner belief system.
Jexans are "cultural" Returners, without a strong belief system, but interested in ancient culture, sometimes easily confused with plain old treasure hunting.

The Dexelites are one of the larger Returner cults. Dexel is thought to have been an author of the Fatunik "Book of Promises", though not all Fatunik scribes agree with this. She is supposedly going to return to the Lands one day with a shining torch, with which she will lead the Faithful to the source of the Old Ways.

The Jexan are another of the larger Returner cults. They are much more diverse and syncretic, adopting and adapting to many different versions of worship/interest-in the ancient past, including things akin to ancestor worship, to fascination with treasure hunting, as well as cargo cult kind of stuff where ancient artifacts are the objects of veneration. Jexa is considered to be the spirit of all things, a somewhat amorphous concept. Not really a god/goddess kind of idea, more like a force that imbues objects -- especially ancient objects -- with energy. 

A sub-group of Jexans venerate Malavorra, the goddess-like southern guru, who is said to personify the spirit of the Setta, referring to her as the Jexan Mother. This makes them one of the most syncretic groups in the Lands.

The Nightingales are a small Returner cult, noteworthy especially for having maintained images of birds in the consciousness of Saskan folks.
