            <Title>Azron Gurk</Title>
            <Text>Azron Gurk
Indeterminate • Here and There, Hither and Yon

Role in Story

Deus-ex-machina, literally. 

A fallen god. A devil. An angel. 

One of the main narrators of the epic, in the form of reports to "Control".
Goal
Likes to fix things that are getting wildly out of tune. A cosmic piano repair man.
A voice for expressing some of the philosophical points outlined in the Notes.
Physical Description
Old man with wild hair. Dresses for the road because he is often traveling or going to obscure places. Carries a number of tools on his person, usually concealed under an overcoat. 

Personality
Diffident but funny.  Aloof but compassionate. 

Occupation
Is a field operative for the Agency with responsibility for both information gathering and occasional interventions.

Habits/Mannerisms
Loves the Saskantinonians, but has been instructed not to get too close to them.  His life-span exceeds most of theirs by many generations. Has been trained that it is best not to get too attached to any one in particular. Nevertheless, he often falls in love or develops strong feelings and has had multiple affairs over the years with both men and women, both beklek, mixten and sint.  His own physical form is the result of Agency engineering. Even Azron has a hard time remembering what his original form was.

Background
Was a robotics/implants repair man on his home planet, which had 18 genders, 12 of which had to interact for new life to germinate. Specialized in ocular and aural enhancing devices. Kind of a cosmic optometrist and hearing-aide specialist. Has a universal translator device.
Internal Conflicts
Sometimes misses his home planet, which was destroyed due to internal conflicts and pollution and was not enclosed in time to save it. Often thinks he should have stayed with the survivors who had left for a nearby planet on a kind of high-tech life-boat, rather than accepting the offer of employment from the Agency. Appreciates the efforts of the Agency to direct the people of this planet in a more sustainable directions. But worries on philosophical/ethical grounds that they are interfering too much.

External Conflicts
Does not get along well with his boss, who is a middle-management dullard. Azron often gets criticized for his tendency to go off script when in the field. 

Story lines



